---
import ContentLayout from '../../layouts/ContentLayout.astro';
import { ZONES } from '../../data/zones';
---

<ContentLayout
  title="Zone Planting Guide"
  description="Find which crops grow best in your USDA hardiness zone. Direct sow vs. indoor start recommendations for Zones 3-10 based on frost-free days."
  breadcrumbs={[{ label: 'Plan', href: '/plan/' }]}
>
  <h1 class="page-title">Zone Planting Guide</h1>
  <p class="page-desc">Select your USDA hardiness zone to see which crops you can direct sow, start indoors, or skip entirely.</p>

  <div class="zone-grid">
    {ZONES.map((z) => (
      <a href={`/zone/${z.zone}/`} class="zone-card glass-card">
        <span class="zone-number">Zone {z.zone}</span>
        <span class="zone-desc">{z.label.replace(`Zone ${z.zone} `, '')}</span>
        <div class="zone-frosts">
          <span>Last frost: {z.lastFrost}</span>
          <span>First frost: {z.firstFrost}</span>
        </div>
        <span class="zone-days">{z.frostFreeDays} frost-free days</span>
      </a>
    ))}
  </div>

  <div class="zone-explainer glass-card">
    <h2>How to use this tool</h2>
    <p>Your USDA hardiness zone is based on your average annual minimum winter temperature. You can look it up at the <a href="https://planthardiness.ars.usda.gov/" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">USDA Plant Hardiness Zone Map</a>.</p>
    <p>Once you know your zone, select it above. For each crop in your zone we show whether it can be direct sown after your last frost date, whether it needs a head start indoors, or whether the season is too short even with indoor starting.</p>
  </div>
</ContentLayout>

<style>
  .page-title {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: var(--text-h1);
    color: var(--color-primary);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-s);
  }

  .page-desc {
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xl);
  }

  .zone-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(240px, 1fr));
    gap: var(--space-l);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xl);
  }

  .zone-card {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-xs);
    padding: var(--space-l);
    text-decoration: none;
    color: inherit;
    transition: transform 0.15s, box-shadow 0.15s;
  }

  .zone-card:hover {
    transform: translateY(-2px);
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-card);
  }

  .zone-number {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: var(--text-h2);
    color: var(--color-primary);
  }

  .zone-desc {
    font-size: var(--text-small);
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    text-transform: capitalize;
  }

  .zone-frosts {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 2px;
    font-size: var(--text-small);
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    margin-top: var(--space-xs);
  }

  .zone-days {
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: var(--text-small);
    color: var(--color-primary-dark);
    margin-top: var(--space-xs);
  }

  .zone-explainer {
    padding: var(--space-xl);
    max-width: 720px;
  }

  .zone-explainer h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    color: var(--color-primary);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-m);
  }

  .zone-explainer p {
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-m);
    line-height: var(--leading-body);
  }

  .zone-explainer a {
    color: var(--color-primary);
  }
</style>

<style>
  .breadcrumb ol {
    display: flex;
    gap: var(--space-xs);
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-m);
    font-size: var(--text-small);
  }

  .breadcrumb li {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: var(--space-xs);
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.7);
  }

  .breadcrumb li:not(:last-child)::after {
    content: '/';
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.4);
  }

  .breadcrumb a {
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.85);
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .breadcrumb a:hover {
